eminism%20to%20explain%20away%20Trump's%20triumph%20over%20two%20women%20in%20less%20than%20a%20decade.%20What%20is%20being%20forgotten%20easily%20here%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20was%20recruited%20in%20a%20huff%20to%20replace%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20who%20was%20sure%20to%20have%20lost%20to%20Trump.%20An%20afterthought.%20The%20Democrats%20were%20desperate%20to%20fight%20anti-incumbency%20but%20addressed%20it%20from%20the%20wrong%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Guilt%20Bait%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20was%20used%20by%20her%20party%20as%20guilt-inducing%20bait%20in%20the%202024%20presidential%20election%2C%20and%20her%20defeat%20has%20important%20lessons%20for%20everyone.%20First%20and%20most%20obviously%2C%20you%20cannot%20guilt-trip%20voters%20into%20supporting%20you%20unconditionally.%20The%20Harris-Walz%20campaign%20doubled%20down%20on%20making%20the%20undecided%20voter%20feel%20guilt-ridden%20for%20even%20considering%20a%20change.%20There%20was%20a%20complete%20lack%20of%20self-awareness%20on%20the%20part%20of%20campaign%20designers%20and%20ideological%20Democrat%20voters%20that%20their%20policies%20may%20have%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20people's%20dissatisfaction.%20Or%20they%20knew%20and%20smugly%20brushed%20it%20off%2C%20armed%20with%20weapons%20of%20collective%20guilt.%20This%20smugness%20caused%20a%20swing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20palpable%20example%20of%20this%20is%20the%20Democrats'%20tone-deafness%20around%20the%20war%20in%20West%20Asia.%20In%20a%20year%20marked%20by%20relentless%20anti-war%20campaigns%20and%20demonstrations%2C%20Democrats%20believed%20Dick%20Cheney%20to%20be%20their%20trump%20card.%20Cheney's%20hawkish%20attitude%20as%20George%20W.%20Bush's%20vice-president%20left%20a%20legacy%20of%20violence%20and%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20the%20US%20and%20everywhere%20else%20the%20country%20intervened%20militarily.%20Harris's%20claims%20to%20usher%20in%20peace%20fell%20flat%20in%20the%20face%20of%20such%20crude%20irony.%20Depending%20on%20how%20disappointed%20or%20angry%20they%20were%2C%20anti-war%20Democrats%20sat%20the%20election%20out%2C%20cross-voted%20for%20Trump%2C%20or%20voted%20for%20the%20third%20alternative%20to%20mark%20their%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThick%20Cosmopolitanism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemocrats'%20adaptation%20of%20what%20political%20scientists%20call%20the%20theory%20of%20%E2%80%98thick%20cosmopolitanism'%20in%20the%20domestic%20domain%20of%20immigration%20did%20not%20work%20in%20securing%20them%20a%20consecutive%20second%20term.%20The%20theory%20argues%20that%20when%20people%20realise%20their%20ingroup's%20culpability%20in%20causing%20harm%20to%20people%20living%20in%20distant%20nations%2C%20they%20adopt%20a%20cosmopolitan%20helping%20demeanour.%20The%20inherent%20limitation%20of%20the%20theory%2C%20as%20demonstrated%20by%20Nicholas%20Faulkner%2C%20and%20the%20revelation%20of%20Democrats'%20hypocrisy%20ensured%20that%20voters%20rejected%20their%20guilt-tripping%20political%20campaign.%20This%20may%20partially%20explain%20why%20a%20substantial%20diaspora%20cohort%20swung%20towards%20Trump.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Democrats%20were%20counting%20on%20brow-beating%20dissent%20with%20guilt.%20Unfortunately%20for%20them%2C%20this%20strategy%20backfired.%20Scholars%20Gunn%20and%20Wilson%20propose%20that%20collective%20guilt%2C%20an%20important%20political%20tool%2C%20is%20often%20undercut%20by%20defensiveness.%20The%20Democratic%20Party%20forgot%20that%20just%20as%20an%20attack%20on%20personal%20identity%20makes%20an%20individual%20defensive%2C%20people%20are%20wont%20to%20react%20with%20defensiveness%20when%20their%20social%20identities%20are%20threatened.%20Calling%20voters%20racist%20and%20sexist%20before%2C%20during%2C%20and%20after%20the%20polls%2C%20Democrats%20inspired%20a%20surge%20of%20defensiveness%20across%20multiple%20demographic%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENobody%20Knew%20What%20Kamala%20Was%20About%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamala%20Harris's%20campaign%20raised%20and%20spent%20more%20money%20than%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20but%20what%20was%20the%20substance%3F%20The%20political%20messaging%20barely%20managed%20to%20escape%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20%E2%80%98Save%20America%20from%20Trump'.%20Reeling%20under%20high%20inflation%20rates%2C%20American%20voters%20felt%20invisible%20when%20no%20concrete%20policy%20measures%20were%20offered%20for%20this%20%E2%80%98Save%20America'%20operation.%20The%20Republicans%20are%20guilty%20of%20running%20the%20same%20banal%20campaign%2C%20but%20they%20had%20anti-incumbency%20on%20their%20side.%20Memories%20of%20Trump's%20previous%20presidency%20were%20fading%2C%20and%20that%20helped%20him.%20Trump's%20campaign%20counted%20on%20the%20fickleness%20of%20public%20memory%20and%20put%20its%20bets%20on%20people's%20ability%20to%20forget%20the%20past%20when%20they%20are%20obsessing%20about%20ongoing%20concerns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeam%20Harris%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20weaponised%20memories%20of%20the%20fractured%20American%20past%20to%20make%20this%20election%20about%20correcting%20historical%20wrongs.%20Psychologists%20warn%20that%20people%20do%20not%20necessarily%20react%20well%20when%20confronted%20with%20problematic%20actions%20of%20their%20own.%20Political%20scientist%20Eunbin%20Chung%20proposed%20in%20the%20context%20of%20East%20Asia%20that%20national%20identity%20affirmation%20can%20be%20employed%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%20way%20of%20disarming%20the%20defensiveness%20that%20is%20prompted%20from%20recognising%20guilt%20of%20one's%20country%2C%20allowing%20more%20prosocial%20responses%20to%20emerge%E2%80%9D.%20Democrats%2C%20however%2C%20fell%20short%20in%20offering%20a%20positive%20spin%20to%20the%20American%20identity%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20counter%20its%20chequered%20racial%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompetitive%20Defensiveness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdd%20to%20this%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20no-limits%20support%20to%20Israel%20despite%20the%20growing%20anti-war%20chime%20even%20within%20the%20rank%20and%20file%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20and%20we%20got%20a%20game%20of%20competitive%20defensiveness%20all%20around.%20The%20leadership%20and%20the%20voters%20stopped%20listening%20to%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20peg%20this%20defeat%20as%20only%20a%20misogynistic%20mistake%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20oversimplifying%20the%20matters.%20This%20is%20how%20Democrats%20wish%20to%20continue%20to%20play%20the%20guilting%20game%20without%20a%20shred%20of%20introspection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nishtha%20Gautam%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731033540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F4sb4k218_kamala-harris_625x300_07_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-did-kamala-harris-lose-because-democrats-guilt-tripped-americans-6969672%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kamala%20Harriss%20campaign%20raised%20and%20spent%20more%20money%20than%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20but%20what%20was%20the%20substance%3F%20The%20political%20messaging%20barely%20managed%20to%20escape%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20Save%20America%20from%20Trump.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-did-kamala-harris-lose-because-democrats-guilt-tripped-americans-6969672%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%201st%20Appointment%20Marks%20A%20Historic%20First.%20Other%20Top%20Contenders%20Are...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUS%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20Thursday%20made%20the%20first%20appointment%20of%20his%20new%20administration%20--%20naming%20a%20chief%20of%20staff%20--%20with%20other%20key%20jobs%20set%20to%20be%20filled%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bdays%20and%20weeks%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20his%20team.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20some%20people%20that%20will%20be%20returning%20(from%20Trump's%20first%20term)%2C%26quot%3B%20senior%20Trump%20aide%20Jason%20Miller%20told%20Fox%20Business%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20there'll%20be%20some%20new%20people%20joining%20the%20mix.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELinda%20McMahon%2C%20a%20former%20CEO%20of%20World%20Wrestling%20Entertainment%2C%20and%20Howard%20Lutnick%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20brokerage%20firm%20Cantor%20Fitzgerald%2C%20are%20leading%20the%20transition%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAFP%20looks%20at%20some%20of%20the%20Trump%20allies%20in%20the%20running%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChief%20of%20Staff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESusie%20Wiles%2C%20his%20election%20campaign%20chief%2C%20became%20Trump's%20first%20appointment%20on%20Thursday%20when%20she%20was%20unveiled%20as%20his%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20as%20widely%20expected.%20Wiles%20enjoys%20wide%20support%20inside%20the%20Trump%20team%20and%20was%20notably%20called%20on%20stage%20by%20the%20incoming%20president%20during%20his%20victory%20speech%20on%20Wednesday%20morning.%20%26quot%3BSusie%20is%20tough%2C%20smart%2C%20innovative%2C%20and%20is%20universally%20admired%20and%20respected%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20of%20the%20steely%2067-year-old%20Florida%20native%2C%20who%20will%20be%20the%20first-ever%20woman%20to%20take%20the%20high-profile%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttorney%20General%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20Trump's%20radical%20agenda%20for%20mass%20deportations%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20and%20his%20ongoing%20legal%20problems%2C%20the%20person%20named%20as%20attorney%20general%20will%20hold%20one%20of%20the%20most%20sensitive%20and%20challenging%20jobs.%20Republican%20Senators%20Mike%20Lee%2C%20Eric%20Schmitt%20and%20John%20Ratcliffe%2C%20Trump's%20former%20director%20of%20national%20intelligence%2C%20were%20reported%20by%20The%20Washington%20Post%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20be%20under%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecretary%20of%20State%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20top%20US%20diplomat%20will%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20implementing%20Trump's%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20first%26quot%3B%20foreign%20policy%2C%20likely%20to%20see%20major%20shifts%20in%20US%20alliances%20and%20forcing%20Ukraine%20into%20negotiations%20with%20Russia.%20Ric%20Grenell%2C%20an%20abrasive%20former%20ambassador%20to%20Germany%20who%20also%20served%20as%20acting%20director%20of%20national%20intelligence%20under%20Trump%2C%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20contender.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20war%2C%20you%20better%20have%20a%20son%20of%20a%20bitch%20as%20the%20secretary%20of%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20March%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BSelf%20Centered%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20openly%20gay%20arch-loyalist%2C%20who%20sought%20to%20overturn%20Trump's%202020%20election%20loss%2C%20appeared%20with%20Trump%20during%20a%20meeting%20with%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20in%20September.%20He%20could%20also%20slot%20into%20the%20crucial%20role%20of%20national%20security%20advisor%2C%20with%20Florida%20Senator%20Marco%20Rubio%2C%20a%20finalist%20to%20become%20Trump's%20running%20mate%2C%20being%20mentioned%20by%20many%20as%20potentially%20secretary%20of%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20am%20interested%20in%20serving%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Rubio%20told%20CNN%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDefense%20secretary%20and%20CIA%20director%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20foreign%20allies%20will%20be%20closely%20following%20the%20nominations%20for%20these%20two%20vital%20positions.%20Kash%20Patel%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Indian%20immigrants%20and%20author%20of%20a%20book%20about%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20mentioned%20as%20a%20future%20CIA%20chief%2C%20as%20has%20ultra-conservative%20Texas%20Senator%20Ratcliffe.%20Arkansas%20Senator%20Tom%20Cotton%2C%20who%20called%20for%20troops%20to%20be%20used%20against%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20protesters%20in%202020%2C%20has%20ruled%20himself%20out%20as%20defense%20secretary%2C%20Axios%20reported%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreasury%20secretary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBillionaire%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20Scott%20Bessent%2C%20a%20key%20donor%20and%20advisor%2C%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20top%20candidate%20to%20be%20the%20next%20treasury%20secretary%20in%20charge%20of%20pushing%20through%20Trump's%20agenda%20of%20low%20taxes%2C%20low%20regulation%20and%20high%20tariffs.%20John%20Paulson%2C%20another%20billionaire%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20and%20advisor%2C%20is%20also%20in%20the%20running%20for%20a%20top%20economic%20portfolio%2C%20as%20is%20Trump%20transition%20co-chair%20Lutnick.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BDOGE%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20surrogate%20and%20Tesla%20boss%20Elon%20Musk%20is%20expected%20to%20lead%20a%20new%20%26quot%3BDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20targeting%20%242%20trillion%20in%20cuts%20from%20the%20federal%20government's%20%247%20trillion%20budget%20--%20although%20no%20one%20has%20explained%20how%20such%20drastic%20cuts%20would%20be%20made.%20The%20world's%20richest%20man%20has%20pledged%20to%20bring%20his%20%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%20management%20style%20to%20Washington%2C%20while%20promising%20%26quot%3Bfair%20and%20humane%26quot%3B%20transitions%20for%20sacked%20federal%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOthers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERobert%20Kennedy%20Jr.%2C%20nephew%20of%20former%20president%20John%20F%20Kennedy%20and%20a%20longtime%20conspiracy%20theorist%2C%20has%20been%20promised%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20role%26quot%3B