-374408%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221107%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIttisha%20celebrates%20a%20clean%20Sangti%20with%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20young%20environmentalists%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20met%20Ittisha%20in%20Delhi%20while%20giving%20a%20talk%20on%20%E2%80%98Ride%20to%20Light%E2%80%99%20%5Ba%20fundraiser%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F315646%2Fmerwyn-coutinho-rajiv-rathod-batti-kits-electricity-in-arunachal-pradesh-remote-villages-video%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Batti%20Project%5D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20I%20explained%20how%20we%20were%20generating%20funds%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Merwyn%20Coutinho%2C%20co-founder%20of%20The%20Batti%20Project%2C%20under%20the%20Further%20and%20Beyond%20Foundation%2C%20which%20has%20illuminated%20several%20remote%20villages%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Bengaluru%2C%20we%20told%20people%20about%20our%20work%20with%20The%20Batti%20Project%20in%20Arunachal%20and%20mentioned%20that%20we%20might%20need%20support.%20Instead%20of%20asking%20for%20donations%2C%20we%20encouraged%20them%20to%20contribute%20by%20donating%20their%20electronic%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20Ittisha%20had%20chosen%20e-waste%20as%20the%20subject%20for%20her%20dissertation.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20many%20people%20were%20researching%20electronic%20waste%20at%20that%20time.%20So%20I%20would%20read%20a%20lot%20of%20research%20papers%20and%20then%20try%20to%20identify%20places%20where%20electronic%20waste%20recycling%20is%20happening%20in%20and%20around%20Delhi.%20Then%20I%20would%20go%20out%20onto%20the%20field%20to%20locate%20the%20places%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20exposing%20her%20to%20e-waste%2C%20her%20on-ground%20work%20during%20her%20thesis%20also%20exposed%20her%20to%20solid%20waste%20and%20the%20many%20problems%20it%20brings%20along%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20per%20a%202021%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments1.worldbank.org%2Fcurated%2Fen%2F823241618991659221%2Fpdf%2FIndia-Sustainable-Solid-Waste-Management-in-Mountain-Areas.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20waste%20generation%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%20388.77%20million%20tonnes%20a%20year%20by%202030.%20The%20ecologically%20sensitive%20Indian%20Himalayan%20Region%20(IHR)%20that%20stretches%20from%20Ladakh%20in%20the%20West%20to%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20East%20is%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20challenges%20this%20may%20bring.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20reveals%20that%20municipal%20solid%20waste%20generation%20in%20IHR%20is%20approximately%2014%2C450%20tonnes%20per%20day%20or%20over%205.2%20million%20tonnes%20per%20year.%20A%20majority%20of%20this%20problem%20plagues%20urban%20centres%2C%20but%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20tourism%20and%20development%20to%20cater%20to%20it%2C%20this%20number%20is%20expected%20to%20rise%20exponentially%20in%20the%20next%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20after%20completing%20her%20dissertation%2C%20Ittisha%20decided%20to%20start%20something%20to%20address%20this%20problem%20in%20the%20Northeastern%20states.%20She%20partnered%20with%20Merwyn%20and%20Rajiv%2C%20initially%20working%20for%20The%20Batti%20Project%2C%20and%20soon%20establishing%20the%20Northeast%20Waste%20Collective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EProject%20Sangti%3A%20A%20community%20takes%20charge%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20journey%20to%20Sangti%20began%20in%202018%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CA%20friend%20who%20runs%20a%20travel%20company%2C%20which%20was%20just%20starting%20out%20at%20the%20time%2C%20reached%20out%20to%20ask%20for%20my%20help.%E2%80%9D%20She%20was%20given%20the%20role%20of%20tour%20instructor%2C%20leading%20a%20group%20of%20school%20students%20to%20a%20summer%20camp.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20something%20about%20this%20place%20%E2%80%94%20it%20felt%20like%20%3Cem%3Edeja%20vu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20river%2C%20the%20valley%2C%20the%20fields%2C%20everything%20seemed%20familiar%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20even%20here%2C%20waste%20was%20a%20noticeable%20problem.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20background%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F345419%2Fbiogas-startup-greeneria-renewable-technology-turns-wet-waste-into-fuel-for-rashtrapati-bhavan-microsoft-hp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaste%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20social%20design%2C%20Ittisha%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20react%20to%20the%20environmental%20challenges%20she%20witnessed%20in%20Sangti.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20I%20could%20do%20was%20conduct%20a%20cleanup%20drive%20with%20the%20help%20of%20the%20kids.%20For%20the%20village%2C%20it%20was%20the%20first%20time%20such%20a%20thing%20was%20happening%2C%20where%20outsiders%20were%20coming%20and%20picking%20up%20their%20trash%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202511px)%20100vw%2C%202511px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222511%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20workshop%20nurturing%20young%20environmentalists%20in%20Sangti%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748.jpg%202511w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-300x226.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-500x376.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-768x578.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-1536x1156.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-2048x1542.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fawareness-session_11zon-1730809748-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374401%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221890%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20workshop%20nurturing%20young%20environmentalists%20in%20Sangti%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20a%20more%20lasting%20impact%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20bamboo%20structure%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20a%20black-necked%20crane%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20growing%20waste%20installation.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20idea%20was%20to%20encourage%20the%20community%20to%20deposit%20their%20waste%20in%20this%20designated%20space%2C%20ensuring%20that%20waste%20is%20contained%20in%20one%20place%20rather%20than%20scattered%20around%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything%20more%20because%20there%20was%20so%20little%20time%20that%20we%20were%20there%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20Guwahati%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20we%20did%20a%20few%20programmes%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Bhalukpong%20and%20Roing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Merwyn%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opportunity%20to%20establish%20a%20community-led%20waste%20management%20system%20in%20Sangti%20arose%20when%20the%20group%20was%20contacted%20by%20community%20members%20seeking%20their%20assistance%20in%20organising%20a%20music%20festival.%20Neither%20Merwyn%20nor%20Ittisha%20were%20enthusiastic%20about%20the%20event.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20environmental%20impact%20of%20these%20festivals%20in%20these%20pristine%20locations%20is%20not%20really%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-500x667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Unsegregated%20waste%20marred%20the%20pristine%20landscape%20of%20Sangti%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-500x667.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-768x1024.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-640x853.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804-150x200.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsangti-in-2020_11zon-1730809804.jpg%201040w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374409%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUnsegregated%20waste%20marred%20the%20pristine%20landscape%20of%20Sangti%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99ve%20been%20part%20of%20many%20festivals%2C%20and%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20found%20them%20to%20be%20beneficial%20unless%20a%20community%20comes%20together%20and%20decides%20on%20something%20more%20meaningful%20for%20their%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20Merwyn%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20I%20told%20them%20that%20if%20you%20want%20to%20create%20a%20community%20programme%2C%20why%20not%20work%20around%20waste%3F%20We%20can%20help%20you%20set%20up%20a%20system%20where%20the%20community%20themselves%20can%20manage%20waste%2C%20and%20this%20festival%20could%20be%20a%20celebration%20of%20that%20achievement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20explained%20to%20the%20community%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20see%20the%20point%20in%20people%20from%20the%20city%20coming%20to%20remote%20locations%20to%20watch%20an%20artist%20perform%20who%20is%20also%20from%20the%20same%20city.%20Instead%2C%20how%20about%20having%20tourists%20come%20to%20your%20place%20to%20see%20what%20you%20have%20to%20offer%3F%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20elaborates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSangti%20is%20a%20place%20rich%20in%20culture%20and%20biodiversity%2C%20and%20their%20main%20festival%20is%20Losar%20(Himalayan%20Buddhist%20New%20Year).%20So%20we%20pitched%2C%20%E2%80%98How%20about%20opening%20Losar%20to%20the%20world%3F%E2%80%99%20to%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%20After%20giving%20it%20a%20thought%2C%20the%20community%20members%20of%20Sangti%20agreed%20and%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20Further%20and%20Beyond%20Foundation%20and%20the%20Northeast%20Waste%20Collective%20came%20together%20to%20partner%20with%20Hum%20(an%20initiative%20working%20to%20create%20community-driven%20ecologically-regenerative%20systems)%20and%20Namgey%20Khandu%20(a%20community%20member%20of%20Sangti%20village)%20to%20organise%20the%20Monyul%20Gathering%20in%20February%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIttisha%20and%20Merwyn%20took%20this%20opportunity%20to%20introduce%20the%20concept%20of%20waste%20management%20to%20the%20community.%20By%20the%20beginning%20of%202020%2C%20Sangti%20had%20started%20treading%20the%20path%20to%20becoming%20a%20zero-waste%20village.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20festival%2C%20we%20set%20up%20the%20initial%20foundation%20for%20the%20waste%20management%20programme%20that%20is%20operational%20in%20Sangti%2C%E2%80%9D%20Merwyn%20informs.%20%E2%80%9CSangti%20had%20become%20litter-free%20around%20that%20time.%20We%20built%20a%20mini%20facility%20where%20we%20could%20store%20the%20waste.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20long%20before%20COVID%20hit%20and%20the%20pandemic%20disrupted%20months%20of%20hard%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EOvercoming%20obstacles%3A%20Sangti%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20a%20zero-waste%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20the%20pandemic%20struck%2C%20there%20was%20a%20pause%2C%E2%80%9D%20Merwyn%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20trying%20to%20raise%20funds%20through%20the%20Government%20to%20support%20the%20community%20in%20terms%20of%20infrastructure%20and%20other%20needs%2C%20but%20it%20failed%20miserably.%20The%20money%20was%20sanctioned%2C%20but%20not%20all%20of%20it%20reached%20the%20community.%20There%20was%20some%20corruption%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20lockdown%20was%20lifted%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20Sangti%20to%20assess%20the%20situation.%20Upon%20their%20return%20in%202022%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Northeast%20Waste%20Collective%20realised%20that%20they%20were%20back%20to%20square%20one.%20Ittisha%20and%20Merwyn%20reinstated%20the%20programme.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20tried%20to%20identify%20new%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20new%20community%20members%20who%20could%20take%20responsibility%20and%20lead%20this%20task%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20Merwyn%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20however%2C%20Merwyn%20chose%20to%20distance%20himself%20from%20the%20project%20and%20Ittisha%20took%20full%20responsibility.%20By%20January%202023%2C%20Ittisha%20rented%20a%20house%20in%20Sangti%20and%20made%20the%20village%20her%20base.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20had%20to%20do%20it%20all%20by%20myself%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20the%20kind%20of%20work%20we%E2%80%99re%20trying%20to%20do%20in%20Sangti%20requires%20driving%20a%20behavioural%20change%20and%20that%20it%20cannot%20be%20done%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20elaborates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-500x667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Community%20members%20working%20together%20to%20keep%20Sangti%20clean%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-500x667.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-768x1024.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-1152x1536.jpg%201152w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-640x853.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765-150x200.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcollection-of-waste_11zon-1730809765.jpg%201161w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374403%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECommunity%20members%20working%20together%20to%20keep%20Sangti%20clean%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20started%20handling%20the%20project%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20few%20volunteers.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20aim%20was%20to%20design%20a%20community-led%20waste%20management%20system.%20But%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20narrow%20down%20any%20single%20model%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20waste%20management%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2Fweb-stories%2Ffrozen-rivers-majestic-peaks-a-perfect-vacation-eight-himalayan-treks-for-your-winter-adventure%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%20mountain%20villages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20do%20is%20ensure%20that%20all%20waste%20generated%20is%20managed%2C%20even%20if%20the%20community%20isn%E2%80%99t%20able%20to%20do%20it%20at%20this%20point%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20manage%20it%20for%20them%20while%20also%20identifying%20challenges%20and%20designing%20a%20system%20that%20the%20community%20could%20lead.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorking%20closely%20with%20the%20villagers%2C%20Ittisha%20successfully%20established%20the%20foundations%20for%20a%20model%20that%20incorporated%20local%20traditions%20and%20ensured%20effective%20waste%20segregation%20and%20management%20without%20relying%20on%20external%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99ve%20been%20engaging%20with%20the%20community%20and%20trying%20to%20create%20awareness%20while%20also%20ensuring%20waste%20segregation%20at%20the%20source%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akriti%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20the%20basic%20idea%20of%20the%20community-led%20waste%20management%20model.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20social%20innovation%20project%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20if%20we%20continue%20and%20expand%20it%20to%20other%20areas%2C%20it%20can%20have%20a%20positive%20impact%2C%20at%20least%20from%20an%20awareness%20standpoint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECommunity-driven%20model%3A%20The%20success%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20was%20to%20ensure%20complete%20waste%20segregation%20at%20the%20source.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20achieved%20this%20in%20every%20household%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20collection%20process%2C%20a%20committee%20of%20four%20women%20and%20four%20men%20was%20established%20to%20oversee%20the%20collection%20of%20waste%20from%20households.%20The%20committee%20members%20take%20turns%20collecting%20the%20waste%20and%20transporting%20it%20to%20the%20Materials%20Recovery%20Facility%20(MRF).%20To%20make%20waste%20management%20less%20burdensome%20for%20the%20community%20members%2C%20Ittisha%20decided%20to%20integrate%20it%20into%20the%20local%20traditions%20of%20the%20Monpa%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20tried%20to%20co-design%20this%20with%20the%20community%20in%20a%20way%20that%20no%20one%20really%20feels%20burdened%20with%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20says.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20should%20be%20as%20easy%20and%20as%20convenient%20for%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Monpas%20have%20four%20to%20five%20holy%20days%20a%20month%20according%20to%20their%20Buddhist%20lunar%20calendar.%20On%20these%20days%2C%20they%20do%20not%20even%20farm%2C%20and%20essentially%2C%20the%20days%20are%20observed%20as%20holidays.%20Three%20of%20these%20days%20%E2%80%94%20the%208th%2C%2015th%2C%20and%2030th%20%E2%80%94%20were%20designated%20for%20specific%20waste%20management%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%208th%20of%20every%20month%20has%20been%20designated%20as%20Social%20Service%20Day.%20On%20this%20day%2C%20one%20person%20from%20every%20household%20is%20mandated%20to%20participate%20in%20cleaning%20up%20their%20respective%20colonies.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20appointed%20colony-in-charges%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20informs%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20are%20responsible%20for%20ensuring%20the%20cleanup%20drive%20operates%20smoothly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2015th%20and%20the%2030th%20are%20dedicated%20to%20waste%20collection.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20built%20a%20convergence%20with%20the%20regional%20sheep%20breeding%20farm%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20idea%20was%20to%20minimise%20our%20dependency%20on%20external%20support%20and%20try%20and%20share%20resources%20that%20are%20already%20there%20within%20the%20community.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20step%20was%20a%20secondary%20segregation%20process%2C%20which%20takes%20place%20at%20the%20village%E2%80%99s%20MRF.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20able%20to%20integrate%20100%20plus%20women%20from%20self-help%20groups%20who%20volunteer%20their%20time%20and%20effort%20to%20do%20the%20secondary%20segregation%20of%20the%20dry%20waste%20that%20is%20collected%20from%20households%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20two%20PLFs%20%E2%80%94%20Sangti%20Valley%20and%20Namdroling%20%E2%80%94%20have%20taken%20charge%20of%20secondary%20segregation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20help%20of%20the%20SHG%20women%2C%20we%20segregate%20the%20waste%20further%20at%20the%20MRF%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dechen%20Paldon%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Namjoling%20PLF%2C%20says.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20divide%20the%20waste%20based%20on%20its%20composition%20and%20structure.%20Bottles%2C%20plastics%2C%20etc%20are%20separated%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201411px)%20100vw%2C%201411px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221411%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ittisha%20and%20some%20members%20of%20the%20Namjoling%20PLF%20team%20working%20together%20for%20a%20cleaner%20Sangti%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819.jpg%201411w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsegregation-with-Namdroling-PLF_11zon-1730809819-150x112.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374411%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221058%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIttisha%20and%20some%20members%20of%20the%20Namjoling%20PLF%20team%20working%20together%20for%20a%20cleaner%20Sangti%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20talks%20about%20the%20challenges%20they%20face%20during%20monsoons%20when%20the%20water%20can%20aid%20the%20growth%20of%20pests%20in%20the%20sacks.%20%E2%80%9CSometimes%20some%20people%20miss%20segregating%20the%20waste%20properly%2C%20or%20due%20to%20rains%2C%20insects%20and%20pests%20fill%20the%20sacks%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dechen%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CSometimes%20it%20discourages%20women%2C%20and%20they%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20work.%20But%20in%20my%20PLF%2C%20I%20talk%20to%20them%20and%20tell%20them%20we%20are%20doing%20good%20and%20it%20will%20take%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDechen%20expresses%20immense%20pride%20in%20being%20able%20to%20participate%20in%20keeping%20their%20village%20waste-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20it%20used%20to%20be%20very%20dirty%20here.%20No%20matter%20where%20you%20looked%2C%20you%20could%20see%20plastics%20and%20bottles%20thrown.%20But%20today%20there%20is%20a%20huge%20improvement%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9COf%20course%2C%20there%20are%20challenges%2C%20but%20we%20try%20to%20keep%20the%20women%20constantly%20motivated%20so%20that%20we%20can%20continue%20the%20good%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20hopeful%20that%20as%20time%20progresses%20and%20the%20team%20is%20able%20to%20improve%20infrastructure%2C%20the%20process%20will%20become%20easier%20and%20see%20more%20active%20participation%20from%20the%20community%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20working%20closely%20with%20the%20community%2C%20Ittisha%20was%20also%20able%20to%20convince%20the%20%3Cem%3EGaun%20Bura%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%3Cem%3Epanchayat%3C%2Fem%3E%20head)%20to%20put%20in%20place%20a%20penalty%20system%20for%20those%20missing%20community%20work%20on%20the%20three%20designated%20days%20without%20a%20genuine%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20of%20work%20has%20gone%20behind%20organising%2C%20framing%2C%20and%20passing%20these%20rules%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20is%20hopeful%20that%20as%20more%20funds%20come%20in%2C%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20improve%20the%20infrastructure%20of%20the%20MRF%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20logistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20always%20been%20challenging%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ittisha%20acknowledges.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20get%20people%20to%20work%20with%20waste%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20lot%2C%20especially%20the%20dry%20waste%20segregation%20bit.%20The%20whole%20thing%20will%20become%20easier%20when%20our%20infrastructure%20improves%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20tourism%20conundrum%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20part%20of%20the%20Eastern%20Himalayan%20ranges%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20is%20among%20the%20most%20picturesque%20tourist%20destinations%20in%20India.%20As%20the%20easternmost%20state%2C%20it%20is%20the%20first%20Indian%20land%20to%20greet%20the%20morning%20sun%2C%20earning%20the%20nickname%20%E2%80%98Land%20of%20the%20Dawn-lit%20Mountains%E2%80%99.%20But%20with%20a%20higher%20influx%20of%20tourists%2C%20the%20ecologically%20sensitive%20region%20will%20inevitably%20see%20an%20exponential%20increase%20in%20waste%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESangti%20village%20is%20no%20exception.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20accommodate%20and%20invite%20tourists%2C%20new%20buildings%20and%20infrastructure%20can%20be%20seen%20coming%20up%20in%20Sangti%2C%20gradually%20transforming%20it%20into%20a%20more%20urbanised%20area.%20This%20growth%20brings%20with%20it%20the%20challenge%20of%20managing%20increased%20waste%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20you%20know%20Sangti%20is%20an%20upcoming%20tourist%20hub%2C%20and%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20homestays%20that%20are%20mushrooming%20there.%20Geographically%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20blessed%20and%20beautiful%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akriti%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20scope%20for%20tourism%20there%3B%20lots%20of%20restaurants%20and%20campsites%20have%20come%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%20problem%2C%20the%20West%20Kameng%20administration%20is%20actively%20working%20to%20spread%20awareness.%20%E2%80%9CFirst%20and%20foremost%2C%20it%20is%20the%20community%20that%20needs%20to%20take%20the%20lead%3B%20only%20the%20communities%20can%20educate%20the%20tourists%20not%20to%20litter%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akriti%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20community-driven%20areas%2C%20and%20here%20the%20feeling%20of%20community%20is%20quite%20high.%20Communities%20have%20been%20sensitised%20not%20to%20let%20tourists%20litter%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20we%20have%20designated%20places%20where%20plastic%20waste%20can%20be%20stored.%20We%20then%20collect%20it%20and%20dispose%20of%20it%20at%20the%20appropriate%20site%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPema%20Sangay%20%E2%80%94%20who%20runs%20a%20homestay%20in%20the%20village%20and%20has%20actively%20embraced%20the%20zero-waste%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20says%20that%20all%20his%20guests%20are%20educated%20about%20the%20village%E2%80%99s%20zero-waste%20initiative%20and%20requested%20to%20keep%20their%20waste%20segregated%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202648px)%20100vw%2C%202648px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Spreading%20awareness%2C%20one%20doorstep%20at%20a%20time%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788.jpg%202648w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-1536x864.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-2048x1152.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FDoor-to-door-campaign_11zon-1730809788-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374407%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221489%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESpreading%20awareness%2C%20one%20doorstep%20at%20a%20time%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElab